  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients suffering from a rupture of the anterior cruciate ligament (ACL) with instability of
      the knee joint are treated with an operative ACL-reconstruction: one group of patients with a
      reconstruction with an autograft tendon (hamstrings), the other group with a reconstruction
      with an allograft tendon (tibialis posterior). The same surgical technique, the same fixation
      technique and the same rehabilitation protocol will be used in both groups. Follow-up will be
      done during 2 years.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
